fectionism is endorsed, many of the standard objections to perfectionism are shown to fail to reach their target. Different arguments in favour of liberal perfectionism are then proposed and critically examined, but the resilience of some pragmatic arguments against liberal perfectionism is conceded. The book ends by showing that perfectionism can be surprisingly relevant for discussions of social justice and proceeds to draw a sketch of the perfectionist implications for questions of distributive justice.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aLiberalismxPhilosophy. 0aPerfection. 0aSocial justice. 4aGutes Leben. 4aPerfektionismus. 4aSoziale Gerechtigkeit. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aPolitical perfectionism.  asocial justice.  athe good life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103729840 cprintz978311033526240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033695540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110336955423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110336955/original  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS